  "explanation": "Use two pointers. One to read consecutive chars, and one to write. If a char appears once, write the char. If more, write char followed by its frequency as separate characters.",
  "answer": "def compress(chars):\n    i = 0; res = 0\n    while i < len(chars):\n        j = i\n        while j < len(chars) and chars[j] == chars[i]: j += 1\n        chars[res] = chars[i]; res += 1\n        if j - i > 1:\n            for c in str(j - i):\n                chars[res] = c; res += 1\n        i = j\n    return res",
